sections.text:
As used in the Adult Community Corrections Act:

A. "department" means the corrections department;

B. "fund" means the community corrections grant fund;

C. "program" means a community-based program that is operated by a county, municipality, the department or a private organization, individually or jointly, with the purpose of providing services to criminal offenders;

D. "criminal offender" means any person convicted of a felony; and

E. "volunteer services" means services provided by individuals or organizations without compensation.

History:Laws 1983, ch. 202, § 2; 1987, ch. 341, § 1; 1988, ch. 101, § 33; 1989, ch. 219, § 2.

The 1989 amendment,effective July 1, 1989, inserted "Adult" in the undesignated introductory paragraph.
